that I want to run by you. So one is just,  

445
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:10,320
what are some of the most impactful 
and recurring pieces of advice that  

446
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:14,960
you share with early career product 
people that you find most helps them  

447
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:19,600
get unstuck and most helps them move to 
where they want to move in their career?

448
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:31,040
One is go to a job where you can ship multiple 
products as fast as possible. Comes back to cycle  

449
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:37,040
time where you can ... Let's say over a period 
of two to three years, you can go through three  

450
00:41:37,040 --> 00:41:44,400
to five product cycles as fast as possible because 
you want to put that under your belt. Don't worry  

451
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:49,280
too much about how you show up in a room. Don't 
try to spend too much time on being the smartest  

452
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:54,880
guy in the room. Just define the product, work 
with your engineering, with your design team,  

453
00:41:54,880 --> 00:41:59,440
with your data team and ship that product. 
Rev that product, iterate on that product,  

454
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:05,360
ship the next product. What you will find as 
you do that over those two to three years,  

455
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:10,880
three years later, you'll suddenly realize 
that, "Wow, I've actually shipped a lot." 

456
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:16,560
And the other thing that I strongly believe is 
what makes a great product manager is not the  

457
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:24,160
five amazing strategic ideas you had over those 
three years. It's the thousand micro decisions  

458
00:42:24,160 --> 00:42:29,360
that you made, not the five macro decisions that 
you made, but the thousand micro decisions that  

459
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:34,640
you made. Where should I put the button? Should I 
put the screen there or not? What should the copy  

460
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:41,200
say? Do I launch this product in Atlanta or in New 
Jersey? You go through these and what you want at  

461
00:42:41,200 --> 00:42:48,080
the end of that is you'll start developing 
an innate sense of judgment. So you want to  

462
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:52,480
increase your cycle time to be able to get to 
judgment as fast as possible, because when you  

463
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:58,000
make a similar decision the 10th time, you don't 
even have to think about it. It just happens. 

464
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:05,040
And we constantly talk about experimentation 
versus gut or data versus gut. As you progress  

465
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:10,400
in your career, you want to develop that gut 
as fast as possible, because in my opinion,  

466
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:14,880
that's what differentiates a good product 
manager from a great product manager,  

467
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:19,120
that they have developed some extra level 
of gut and they're able to make the correct  

468
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:23,280
decisions because of the experience 
that they have had over that time.

469
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:27,840
Another way to label what you're describing 
as product sense, which is something a lot of  

470
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:32,960
people are always told they should be building 
and are very unsure how to go about building it.  

471
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:36,720
And what I love about your advice here 
is this, is you find a place where you  

